---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
export const prerender = true;
const title = "Terms of Service \u2014 Numetal";
const description = "Terms of Service for numetal.xyz, the Numetal Discord application, and the Numetal protocol.";
const canonical = "https://numetal.xyz/";
const bodyHtml = `<style>
  :root{--ikb:#002FA7;--paper:#FAFAF8;--ink:#141414;--cyan:#0791a6;--hard:#8c8c8c;--orange:#FF5A1F;--line:#cfcfcf;--muted:#7c7c7c;--mono:ui-monospace,'SF Mono','SFMono-Regular',Menlo,Consolas,monospace;--sans:'Helvetica Neue',Helvetica,Arial,'Liberation Sans',sans-serif}
  *{box-sizing:border-box;margin:0;padding:0}
  html{-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased}
  body{background:var(--paper);color:var(--ink);font-family:var(--sans);font-size:15px;line-height:1.6;min-height:100vh;display:flex;flex-direction:column}
  a{color:var(--ikb)}
  .wrap{width:100%;max-width:760px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 24px}
  .dither{height:11px;background-image:radial-gradient(#191919 .62px,transparent .72px);background-size:3px 3px}
  header{border-bottom:1px solid var(--ink)}
  .bar0{display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;height:56px;max-width:760px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 24px}
  .mark{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:9px;font-family:var(--mono);font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.06em}
  .mark a{color:var(--ink);text-decoration:none}
  .mark .sq{width:13px;height:13px;background:var(--ikb)}
  .tagh{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted)}
  main{flex:1;padding:48px 0 64px}
  h1{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:32px;letter-spacing:-.01em;margin-bottom:6px}
  .upd{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:12px;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:30px}
  h2{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:14px;letter-spacing:.03em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:30px 0 10px;display:flex;gap:9px;align-items:center}
  h2 .n{color:var(--ikb)}
  p,li{margin-bottom:12px;color:#222}
  ul{padding-left:20px}
  strong{color:var(--ink)}
  .risk{border:1px solid var(--ink);padding:16px 18px;margin:8px 0;font-size:14px}
  footer{background:#fff;margin-top:48px}
  .foot{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:12px;font-size:11px;color:var(--muted);padding:22px 0}
  .foot a{color:var(--muted)}
  .flinks{display:flex;gap:14px;flex-wrap:wrap;justify-content:flex-end}
  .foot a{color:var(--muted)}
</style>

<header><div class="bar0">
  <div class="mark"><span class="sq"></span><a href="https://numetal.xyz">NUMETAL</a></div>
  <div class="tagh">Terms</div>
</div></header>
<div class="dither"></div>

<main><div class="wrap">
  <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
  <div class="upd">Last updated: 11 June 2026</div>

  <p>These Terms of Service (“Terms”) govern your use of the website at <strong>numetal.xyz</strong>, the <strong>Numetal Discord application</strong> (the “bot”), and related software and on-chain components (together, the “Services”), operated by Numetal (“we”, “us”).</p>

  <h2><span class="n">01</span>Acceptance</h2>
  <p>By using the Services you agree to these Terms. If you do not agree, do not use the Services.</p>

  <h2><span class="n">02</span>The Services</h2>
  <p>Numetal is <strong>experimental</strong> software — a protocol for verification of autonomous agent work, together with community tooling such as the moderation bot and informational pages. The Services are provided on an “as is” and “as available” basis and may change, break, or be discontinued at any time.</p>

  <h2><span class="n">03</span>Acceptable use</h2>
  <p>You agree not to misuse the Services, including: attempting to disrupt, attack, or gain unauthorized access; using them for unlawful purposes; or interfering with other users. Server administrators are responsible for how they configure and use the bot within their own communities. numetal.xyz hosts <strong>no user-generated content and accepts no uploads</strong>; report any suspected abuse or illegal content to <strong>contact@numetal.xyz</strong> and we will act on valid reports.</p>

  <h2><span class="n">04</span>Restricted jurisdictions &amp; sanctions</h2>
  <p>You may not use the Services if you are located in, ordinarily resident in, or accessing them from a jurisdiction subject to comprehensive sanctions, or if you are a person or entity on a restricted-party or sanctions list administered by the U.S. Office of Foreign Assets Control (OFAC), the United Nations Security Council, the European Union, the United Kingdom, or any comparable authority. Restricted jurisdictions currently include <strong>Cuba, Iran, North Korea, Syria, and the Crimea, Donetsk, and Luhansk regions of Ukraine</strong>, and may change as sanctions programs evolve. By using the Services, you represent that you are <strong>not a Restricted Person</strong> and that you will not use the Services for any prohibited purpose or for the benefit of any sanctioned or restricted party.</p>

  <h2><span class="n">05</span>No financial, investment, or legal advice</h2>
  <div class="risk">
    <p>Nothing in the Services is financial, investment, legal, or tax advice. <strong>$NUMETAL and any related tokens or assets are experimental and may lose all of their value.</strong> On-chain transactions are irreversible. Markets are volatile. Do your own research and participate only with what you can afford to lose entirely.</p>
  </div>

  <h2><span class="n">06</span>No warranty</h2>
  <p>The Services are provided without warranties of any kind, whether express or implied, including merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement. We do not warrant that the Services will be uninterrupted, secure, or error-free.</p>

  <h2><span class="n">07</span>Limitation of liability</h2>
  <p>To the maximum extent permitted by law, Numetal and its contributors shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or exemplary damages, or for any loss of funds, tokens, data, or profits, arising from your use of (or inability to use) the Services.</p>

  <h2><span class="n">08</span>The Discord bot</h2>
  <p>The bot is provided to server administrators as a moderation tool. You are responsible for granting it permissions, configuring it, and the moderation actions taken in your server. We are not responsible for actions performed by your moderators using the bot.</p>

  <h2><span class="n">09</span>Third-party services</h2>
  <p>The Services rely on third parties (including Discord, Cloudflare, the Base network, and on-chain liquidity venues) each governed by their own terms. We are not responsible for third-party services.</p>

  <h2><span class="n">10</span>Changes</h2>
  <p>We may update these Terms from time to time. The “last updated” date reflects the current version. Continued use after a change constitutes acceptance.</p>

  <h2><span class="n">11</span>Governing law</h2>
  <p>These Terms are governed by generally applicable principles of international commercial and consumer-protection law, without regard to conflict-of-laws principles. Any mandatory consumer-protection rights you hold under the law of your country of residence remain unaffected, and nothing here deprives you of them.</p>

  <h2><span class="n">12</span>Community, Telegram &amp; verification bot</h2>
  <p>Access to the official Numetal Telegram community is <strong>token-gated</strong> and managed by our verification bot (<strong>@numetalguard_bot</strong>). By requesting to join or using the bot you agree that:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Verification is a free, off-chain wallet signature</strong> — you sign a message to prove wallet ownership. It is <strong>not a transaction</strong>, moves no funds, grants no token approvals, and never takes custody. We will <strong>never</strong> ask for your seed phrase, private keys, or any payment to verify.</li>
    <li><strong>Holding requirement:</strong> entry and continued access require holding the stated minimum of $NUMETAL (and/or designated assets). Thresholds may change; balances are re-checked periodically, and access may be revoked if your balance falls below the minimum.</li>
    <li><strong>Data:</strong> to enforce access we link your Telegram ID to the wallet address you verify, stored solely for membership management and not sold. See the <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.</li>
    <li><strong>Conduct:</strong> no impersonation of the team, the bot, or members; no scams, phishing, or spam. Violations result in removal and ban.</li>
    <li><strong>Official channels only:</strong> the team and the bot will <strong>never DM you first</strong> to request funds, keys, or "wallet validation." The only official bot is <strong>@numetalguard_bot</strong>; the only official $NUMETAL contract is <code>0x57EDb7FC54ADa9Ef4E113DC05A168449e63cFbA3</code>. Anything else is an impostor.</li>
    <li>Token-gating is <strong>access control, not investment solicitation</strong>; nothing here is financial advice.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2><span class="n">13</span>Contact</h2>
  <p>Questions about these Terms: reach us in the official Numetal Discord, or at <strong>contact@numetal.xyz</strong>.</p>
</div></main>

<footer><div class="wrap foot">
  <span>Numetal · an <a href="https://gokhan.vc" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Atelier&nbsp;Gökhan</a> studio · agents across onchain, compute &amp; culture</span>
  <span class="flinks">
    <a href="https://gokhan.vc" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Atelier Gökhan</a>
    <a href="https://github.com/gokhan-vc" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>
    <a href="https://gokhanturhan.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">gokhanturhan.com</a>
    <a href="/feed.xml">RSS</a>
    <a href="/sitemap.xml">Sitemap</a>
    <a href="/llms.txt">llms.txt</a>
    <a href="https://numetal.xyz/terms">Terms</a>
    <a href="https://numetal.xyz/privacy">Privacy</a>
    <a href="/cookies">Cookies</a>
  </span>
</div></footer>
`;
---
<Base title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <Fragment set:html={bodyHtml} />
</Base>
